info.author: Intel Corporation
info.description:
Intel (R) Integrated Performance Primitives (Intel(R) IPP) provides developers with high-quality, production-ready, low-level building blocks for image processing, signal processing, and data processing (data compression and decompression) applications. This package provides C programming language interfaces. Intel IPP C language interfaces can be called from applications written in either C or C++, as well as in any other language that can reference a C interface. See also:
* Release notes ([https://software.intel.com/content/www/us/en/develop/articles/intel-ipp-release-notes-and-new-features.html](https://software.intel.com/content/www/us/en/develop/articles/intel-ipp-release-notes-and-new-features.html)).
* One of many Intel(R) accelerated Python packages and performance library runtimes available on  [PyPI]([https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/installing-the-intel-distribution-for-python-and-intel-performance-libraries-with-pip-and](https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/installing-the-intel-distribution-for-python-and-intel-performance-libraries-with-pip-and)), and as part of  [Intel(R) Distribution for Python]([https://software.intel.com/en-us/distribution-for-python](https://software.intel.com/en-us/distribution-for-python)).
* For latest release updates and security notifications, please  [subscribe]([https://software.intel.com/en-us/forums/intel-distribution-for-python](https://software.intel.com/en-us/forums/intel-distribution-for-python)) to the Intel(R) Distribution for Python Community forum.
